' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
'  Inheritance & Implementation Relationships
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────

' Span hierarchy
Span --|> OtelApiSpan : extends
Span ..|> ReadWriteSpanInterface : implements

' SpanBuilder implements OTel API contract
SpanBuilder ..|> SpanBuilderInterface : implements

' SpanContext implements OTel API contract
SpanContext ..|> SpanContextInterface : implements

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
'  Composition & Dependency Relationships
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────

' SpanBuilder holds internal state
SpanBuilder *-- TracerSharedState : holds
SpanBuilder ..> SpanContext : creates via\ncreateFromLocalSpan()
SpanBuilder ..> Span : creates via\nstartSpan()

' Span bridges to DDTrace internals
Span *-- SpanData : bridges\n(getDDSpan())

' Convention & TraceAnalyticsProcessor use internals
Convention ..> SpanData : reads meta\n& span kind
Convention ..> Tag : uses constants
TraceAnalyticsProcessor ..> Tag : uses ANALYTICS_KEY

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
'  Notes
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────

note right of Span
  **DDTrace-to-OTel Bridge**
  getDDSpan() exposes internal DDTrace\\SpanData
  for interoperability with the Datadog tracing engine.
  endOTelSpan() is the DDTrace-aware shutdown path.
end note

note right of SpanBuilder
  **startSpan() flow:**
  1. applySpanKind() → sets Tag::SPAN_KIND
  2. Resolve parent ContextInterface
  3. getSampler().shouldSample() → SamplingResult
  4. DDTrace\\start_trace_span() → SpanData
  5. SpanContext::createFromLocalSpan() → SpanContextInterface
  6. Span::startSpan(...) → Span
  If not sampled → Span::wrap(spanContext) (no-op)
end note

note bottom of SpanContext
  **DDTrace-specific factory:**
  createFromLocalSpan() is not part of the OTel spec —
  it creates a SpanContext from a DDTrace\\SpanData,
  supporting W3C traceparent propagation.
end note

note bottom of Convention
  **OTel Semantic Conventions → Datadog operation names:**
  http.request.method + SERVER → 'http.server.request'
  db.system + CLIENT → '{db.system}.query'
  rpc.system + CLIENT → '{rpc.system}.client.request'
  messaging.system + operation → '{system}.{operation}'
  fallback → ''
end note

